Volkswagen (VW) Group, on Tuesday said it would temporarily shut down production at the vast majority of its plants from Friday in response to the coronavirus pandemic. Sources from the German auto giant’s works council disclosed this in Hanova.
Europe’s largest carmaker reported a boost in profits for its core VW passenger cars brand in 2019, but warned of a very difficult year ahead. According to the Chairman of the Management Board, Herbert Diess, the corona pandemic presents the company with unknown operational and financial challenges.